The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease dated 31 May 2019:
Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 1982, of which 1888 are confirmed and 94 are probable. In total, there were 1332 deaths (1238 confirmed and 94 probable) and 531 people healed.
-350 suspected cases under investigation;
-8 new confirmed cases, including 3 in Butembo, 2 in Beni, 2 in Katwa and 1 in Mangurujipa;
-9 new confirmed case deaths, including 4 community deaths, including 2 in Beni, 1 in Mangurujipa and 1 in Butembo; 5 deaths at CTE, including 3 in Katwa and 2 in Mandima;
-6 new healings from the CTE, including 4 in Mandima, 1 in Beni and 1 in Butembo.

